Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Secretary of War Suite in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. She thanked the leaders present for their work in addressing the climate crisis and emphasized the urgency of the situation. Harris discussed the Build Back Better Agenda, which focuses on climate, jobs, family, and health. She highlighted the goal of a 50% reduction in emissions by 2030 and the need for resilience, clean energy, and electric vehicles. Harris also emphasized the importance of environmental justice and shared her personal experiences with environmental issues. She assured the attendees of the administration's commitment to these issues and acknowledged the ongoing negotiations. Harris concluded by recognizing the role of external pressure in driving progress and thanked the leaders for their efforts.